academics stanford university school of education leadership degree programs skip to main content skip to main navigation stanford university school of education leadership degree programs pols joint ma mba search this site pols go to joint ma mba program academics pols projects admissions students & alumni faculty & research school news home pols academics academics as a pols student you will be required to complete 45 units of coursework within three consecutive quarters the pols program is divided into three concentrations of specialization which are further sub divided into thematic clusters the concentrations are the higher education concentration the prek 12 concentration and the individually designed concentration idc in addition to the core requirements of each concentration there are thematic clusters that span across these concentrations teaching & learning organizational leadership policy systems and inquiry & assessment to ensure that you acquire a broad range of concentrated knowledge and skills while still focusing on a specialization for a visual diagram of how the concentrations and thematic clusters work together please see at a glance you can choose from over 55 courses offered at the school of education as well as a variety of classes offered at other stanford graduate departments all of these courses and the requirements they fulfill are listed on our courses section a 45 unit program consists of approximately 12 15 courses depending on designated course unit values which may run from 1 5 units while it is possible to substitute a non required course for a required course it is not encouraged and the request must go through a petition process however substitutions may be granted if you have recently completed similar graduate coursework such as graduate courses in teaching as part of a teaching credential the substituted course must reflect the academic goals and objectives of the pols program for more information about coursework substitution or unit transfer please visit our faq section academics concentrations degree at a glance thematic clusters internships pols project explore courses stanford university school of education 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 tel 650 723 2109 copyright 2012 stanford university all rights reserved contact suse admissions helpsu maps & directions suse it axess academic calendar stanford bulletin office of the registrar edmail stanfordwho stanfordyou connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr website by lyudmila christie suse it
